article.description: Alexis Rack scored 16 points to lead Mississippi State (No. 25 AP) to an 81-35 victory over Utah Valley on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Rack scores 16 as Mississippi State rolls to win
article.linkText: Mississippi State gets easy win over Utah Valley
article.story:
STARKVILLE, Miss. --  Alexis Rack scored 16 points to lead Mississippi State (No. 25 AP) to an 81-35 victory over Utah Valley on Wednesday night.

The Lady Bulldogs (3-0) forced 33 turnovers and opened the game against the Lady Wolverines (2-2) with a 32-3 run. Utah Valley made only three field goals in the first half and trailed 41-14 at halftime.

Mississippi State connected on a season-high 10 3-pointers and continued to dominate opponents with an average margin of victory of 45 points. The Lady Bulldogs held Utah Valley to 28.6 percent shooting.

Tysheka Grimes added 14 points and six rebounds for Mississippi State and Chanel Mokango and Diamber Johnson each had 10. Rack also had four assists.

Kayla Burningham made three of four 3-pointers and led Utah Valley with 11 points. She was the only Wolverines player to reach double figures.
